Github website link

Github repo:

  • ReadMe.md: Containing bold and italics font for some of the texts, ordered and un-ordered bullets points shows over contents and assignment objectives. Two levels of headers used with title and subtitle. Referencing website links to Color Picker and Image_function.

  • .nojekyll: Containing codes for memes, the other markdown for the assignment detail.

Meme Codes: Using c(), image_blank(), image_read(), image_annotate(), image_append(), image_write() and image_animate(). Pipes %>% used to further develop the image or texts and comments # as referencing.

My meme

# Key features of inspo_meme.png:
# Layout: left size text and right size images
# Text: Bold, Normal font

library(magick)
#image part
after_gym_url <-"https://ih1.redbubble.net/image.5312849102.3231/st,small,507x507-pad,600x600,f8f8f8.jpg"
before_gym_url <- "https://i.ebayimg.com/images/g/R8UAAOSwcu5irXAs/s-l1600.jpg"

before_gym <- image_read(before_gym_url)%>%
  image_scale(250)

after_gym <- image_read(after_gym_url)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#Text part
before_text <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 250, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "before you go to gym \nin winter",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 20, font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

after_text <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 250, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "once you finish workout \nin winter",
                 color = "#000000", font = "Impact",
                 size = 20, gravity = "center")

#presentation part
top <- image_append(c(before_gym, before_text))
bottom <- image_append(c(after_gym, after_text))

#Gathering them
c(top, bottom) %>%
  image_append(stack=TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(250)

library(magick)
after_gym_url <-"https://ih1.redbubble.net/image.5312849102.3231/st,small,507x507-pad,600x600,f8f8f8.jpg"
before_gym_url <- "https://i.ebayimg.com/images/g/R8UAAOSwcu5irXAs/s-l1600.jpg"

before_gym <- image_read(before_gym_url)%>%
  image_scale(250)

after_gym <- image_read(after_gym_url)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#Text part
before_text <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 250, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "before you go to gym \nin winter",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 20, font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

after_text <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 250, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "once you finish workout \nin winter",
                 color = "#000000", font = "Impact",
                 size = 20, gravity = "center")

#presentation part
top <- image_append(c(before_gym, before_text))
bottom <- image_append(c(after_gym, after_text))

#Gathering them
second_slide <- c(top, bottom) %>%
  image_append(stack=TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(250)

# Animatate
first_slide <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 250, color = "#000000")%>%
  image_annotate("ðŸ¥¶Uni Students Daily", color = "#ffffff", font = "Impact",
                 size = 20, gravity = "center")

# third slide
third_slide <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 250, color = "#000000")%>%
  image_annotate("ðŸ“Outside gym", color = "#ffffff", font = "Impact",
                 size = 20, gravity = "center")

#fourth_slide
hotdog_sus_pic <- image_read("https://media.tenor.com/Nfct9RreQfUAAAAe/dog-meme.png")%>%
  image_scale("130x130")

me <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 75, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "bro: let's have some bubble teaðŸ§‹",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 20, font = "Impact")

bro <- image_blank(width = 250, height = 75, color = "#ffffff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "me on the cut day: ",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 20, font = "Impact")
gathering <- c(me, bro, hotdog_sus_pic)%>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)
# print(gathering)

#fifth_slide
rock_image <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/4/6j7j8h.jpg")
five <- image_rotate(rock_image, 0)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#sixth_slide
six <- image_rotate(rock_image, 90)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#seventh_slide
seven <- image_rotate(rock_image, 180)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#eighth_slide
eight <- image_rotate(rock_image, 270)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#ninth_slide
nine <- image_rotate(rock_image, 360)%>%
  image_scale(250)

#rock_combo <- c(six, seven, eight, nine)
# summarize animation
frames <- c(first_slide, second_slide, third_slide, gathering, five, six, seven, eight, nine)
final_work <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)%>%
  image_scale(250)


image_write(final_work, "my_animation.gif")

Creativity

CSS Code: From this part, I used body, p and some notations in the beginning in order to decorate the layout of the website. I changed the background color of the whole website by importing image url and the color was light color so that it can present the contents clearly. CSS layout was used in the notation part, it can cast the title part looks not that boring.

Import local image to rmd file: As what we taught, we usually used ![Alt text](url) to fetch the url from external website. In this assignment, it related to import a local image file, which I used ![](File name) in order to import to Rmd file.

Note: the local file should be in the same folder with Rmd file
